snippet.textDisplay:
Matt, you need to ditch the rest of the chrome now. Earl is all black in the back. You have black mirrors and wheels. Now you've added a black ranch hand.

Get a basic black mesh grill. They aren't that expensive.

Get some oem quad halogen headlights with black bezels. They are super cheap and should be plug and play for your truck. Or drop in some oem projectors with black bezels normally found on Sports or Warlocks with the factory "black appearance package" or "night edition"

snippet.textDisplay:
Some quick calculations. If Earl gets stuck at the highest mire factor of 3 then
Earl+cargo weight X,XXX lbs and uses XX,XXX rating winch you will need X number of snatch blocks + gear of XX,XXX load rating

7,000lbs load+12,000lb winch=2 snatch blocks + 12,000lb load rated gear
7,000lbs load+16,000lb winch=2 snatch blocks + 12,000lb load rated gear

8,000lbs load+12,000lb winch=3 snatch blocks + 10,000lb load rated gear
8,000lbs load+16,000lb winch=2 snatch blocks + 14,000lb load rated gear

9,000lbs load+12,000lb winch=3 snatch blocks + 11,000lb load rated gear
9,000lbs load+16,000lb winch=2 snatch blocks + 15,000lb load rated gear

Hope that's useful
